  <h2>The manifestation team determined that my child's behavior was:</h2>
  <p>NOT a manifestation of his or her  disability.</p>
</div>
  <h2>Options: </h2>
  <ol>
  <li>The behavior involved <span class="def" id="drugs">drug*</span> or alcohol possession (not use), <span class="def" id="weapon">weapons*</span> or <span class="def" id="bodily-injury">serious bodily injury*</span>. <a href="/school-discipline-information/504/50-drugs-alcohol-not-manifestation.asp"><br />
  	<br />
  	Continue Here &gt;&gt;&gt;</a></li>
	<div class="tip"> Note: If the behavior involved the use of drugs or alcohol or the behavior involved possession and the school can establish that your child is currently using drugs or alcohol, the protections of Section 504 do not apply and your child may be disciplined the same as a student without a disability.	</div>
    <p class="tip">Note: The district must provide alternative educational  services to the extent a suspension or expulsion exceeds five consecutive  school days. <sup class="statute">1</sup></p>
    
  <li>The behavior did not involve drugs or alcohol, weapons or serious  bodily injury. <a href="/school-discipline-information/504/53-54-no-drugs-alcohol-not-manifestation.asp"><br />
  	<br />
  	Continue Here &gt;&gt;&gt;</a></li>
</ol>
